lizes all\n    21→path resolution and config loading for the multi-milestone orchestrator. Every other T4\n    22→ticket depends on this module existing first.\n    23→\n    24→---\n    25→\n    26→## Acceptance Criteria\n    27→\n    28→- [x] `orchestrator/instance_paths.py` created with:\n    29→  - `InstancePaths` dataclass containing all path fields:\n    30→    - `orch_dir`, `instance_dir`\n    31→    - `config_path` (`orch_dir/config.json`)\n    32→    - `config_local_path` (`orch_dir/config.local.json`)\n    33→    - `state_path`, `activity_log`, `pending_gate_path`, `gate_response_path`, `godot_mcp_lock_path`\n    34→    - `results_dir`, `logs_dir`\n    35→    - `prompts_dir`, `schemas_dir` (shared, under `orch_dir`)\n    36→  - `resolve_instance(instance_name: str, orch_dir: Path | None = None) -> InstancePaths`:\n    37→    - `orch_dir` defaults to `$HFS_ORCH_DIR` env var, then `<repo_root>/orchestrator`\n    38→    - `instance_dir = orch_dir / \"instances\" / instance_name`\n    39→    - Creates `instance_dir`, `instance_dir/results`, `instance_dir/logs` on first call\n    40→    - Returns fully populated `InstancePaths`\n    41→  - `load_config(paths: InstancePaths) -> dict`:\n    42→    - Loads `paths.config_path` (required — raises `FileNotFoundError` if absent)\n    43→    - If `paths.config_local_path` exists, deep-merges it on top of defaults\n    44→    - Returns merged dict\n    45→  - `_deep_merge(base: dict, override: dict) -> dict` — private recursive merge helper\n    46→    - Merges leaf values: override wins; sub-dicts are merged recursively, not replaced\n    47→- [x] Module has no external dependencies beyond stdlib (`pathlib`, `json`, `os`, `dataclasses`)\n    48→- [x] Module is importable from any script in `orchestrator/`\n    49→\n    50→---\n    51→\n    52→## Implementation Notes\n    53→\n    54→- Repo root detection: walk up from `__file__` to find the directory containing `orchestrator/`\n    55→- `_deep_merge` must handle nested 